      <section id="fs-id2627726" class="section-summary">
<title>Section Summary</title><list id="fs-id2689702"><item id="import-auto-id1262679">Photons have momentum, given by <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>p</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mi>h</m:mi><m:mi>λ</m:mi></m:mfrac></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math>, where <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>λ</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> is the photon wavelength.</item>
    <item id="import-auto-id1261926">Photon energy and momentum are related by
 <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>p</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mi>E</m:mi><m:mi>c</m:mi></m:mfrac></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math>, where <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>E</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mstyle fontstyle="italic"><m:mrow><m:mtext>hf</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontstyle="italic"><m:mrow><m:mtext>hc</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mo stretchy="false">/</m:mo><m:mi>λ</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> for a photon.</item>
</list>
    </section>

